Field Detail

PARAM_ENCODING_WORKAROUND

private static final String PARAM_ENCODING_WORKAROUND
Defines the parameter for old MX versions which has the encoding problem for double closing square brackets. Only if this parameter is defined the encoding work around method is executed.

See Also:
execXMLExport(ParameterCache_mxJPO), Constant Field Values

INSERT_TEXT

private static final String INSERT_TEXT

execXMLExport

protected String execXMLExport(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache)
                        throws matrix.util.MatrixException
Return the XML export for programs. Because of 'problems' of old MX versions with the encoding of brackets the original method is overwritten. The special encoding is only done if the parameter PARAM_ENCODING_WORKAROUND is activated.

Overrides:
execXMLExport in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
Returns:
XML string (and for old MX version encoded)
Throws:
matrix.util.MatrixException - if export failed
See Also:
encodeXMLExport(String)

encodeXMLExport

protected String encodeXMLExport(String _xml)
Encodes the XML string which is returned from old MX version. Old MX versions have some problems with not encoded double closed squared brackets. Newer MX versions itself encodes them to REPLACE_TEXT. This is also done from this method for old MX versions.

Parameters:
_xml - XML to encode
Returns:
encoded XML
See Also:
execXMLExport(ParameterCache_mxJPO), REPLACE_TEXT
